folder: Ralph Avenue & Atlantic Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Ralph Avenue, east side, south from Atlantic Avenue to Dean Street. The block from Atlantic Avenue to Pacific Street is occupied by a gasoline station and a used-car lot. The cone-towered building is the Brooklyn Hebrew Orphan Asylum, between Pacific and Dean Streets.
September 13, 1930
P. L. Sperr

folder: Ralph Avenue & Atlantic Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Ralph Ave., e.s., s. fr. Atlantic Ave., B'klyn.
June 5, 1942.
